    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil, </strong>once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk the <strong>creamy stock</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>plant-based béchamel sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
